 earlier article in the harvard business review was excellence in product definition an inside look professor tabrizi received the prestigious administrative science quarterly 2001 award with professor eisenhardt for scholarly contribution for a paper published five years earlier that had the greatest influence on subsequent theory and research in the field of management which includes strategy marketing organization and operation fields he has also received the prestigious school of engineering tau beta pi award among over 200 faculty members for excellence in undergraduate teaching and the industrial engineering and engineering management teacher of the year award in winter 1994 hea s been touted as teaching the first web based course in the world at stanford university dr tabrizi has served as the director of stanford aea mini mba executive program among his notable past and current consulting clients are applied materials hp intel ibm idc nokia motorola lucent stanfordtelecommunication agilent oracle cisco honeywell nortel networks china mobile clarify verisign and several start ups he serves on the board of catapult ventures and has served on the board of ichatterbox com sold to covia inc webmbo merged with realm corp columbusnewport venture capital firm and advisory board of several startups as a frequent traveler to china in the past four years professor tabrizi has held seminars and has advised over 300 ceos of the largest private and public chinese companies on their corporate transformation earlier in his career he worked for ibm as an engineer and was promoted to sales management position professor tabrizi has received a bs in computer engineering from university of kansas ms in electrical and computer engineering from university of illinois urbana and ms in engineering management and a ph d in strategy organizations and technology management from stanford university ieem for more publications please consult chapters and publications last modified tue 7 f